title: MCP Gemini Configuration

!! Connecting Gemini to TiddlyWiki MCP Server

To connect Gemini with a TiddlyWiki instance using the MCP (Model Context Protocol) server, use the following command structure:

!!! Command Line Interface (CLI)

Run the following command in your terminal, replacing `./test` with the path to your TiddlyWiki folder:

```bash
gemini mcp add --scope project tiddlywiki-mcp tiddlywiki ./test --mcp
```

!!! Command Breakdown:

* `--scope project`: Limits the configuration to the current project.
* `tiddlywiki-mcp`: The name assigned to the MCP server.
* `tiddlywiki`: The executable command to run.
* `./test --mcp`: The arguments passed to the command (the wiki path and the `--mcp` flag).

!!! JSON Configuration

The above command generates or updates the `.gemini/settings.json` file with the following configuration:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "tw-mcp": {
      "command": "tiddlywiki",
      "args": [
        "./test",
        "--mcp"
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

!!! Features

Once connected, Gemini can:

* Read and search tiddlers using filters.
* Create, update, and delete tiddlers.
* Render wikitext to HTML or plain text.
* Inspect the internal $tw state and variable scopes.